messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
Remove phone number +12453344098 from my contact
I’ll need a little more to go on—could you tell me the contact’s name or their person_id so I can be sure I’m removing the right entry?
I don't have any more info, just the phone number.

I don’t have a unique match without a person_id or name on file. If you’re sure you want to delete every contact entry that has the phone number +12453344098, I can go ahead and remove all such entries. Would you like me to proceed?
I’m unable to remove a contact by phone number alone— the remove_contact API requires a person_id. Do you have the contact’s person_id (or their name so I can look it up)?
I don't have either, just delete what you can with the number.

I’m sorry, but the system can only delete contacts by their internal person_id (or if you provide their exact name so I can look up the ID). If you don’t have the person_id or name on hand, you’ll need to retrieve that first—perhaps from your phone’s contacts app—and then let me know. Once you have the person_id (or exact name), I can remove the entry for you.
